## Learning Activities and Resources

This week I learned how to create a WordPress child theme using the Twenty Twenty-Five theme. I also learned how to activate the child theme and customise my website without editing the parent theme.

During this week's practical activity, I completed several visible changes to my website, including:

- Changed the website background colour.
- Changed the website text colour.
- Changed the website heading style.
- Changed the button style.
- Changed the website typography.
- Changed the header and footer colours.

These changes improved the appearance of my website while keeping the original theme unchanged.

## Resources Used

- WordPress Developer Documentation
- WordPress Theme Handbook
- Local WordPress
- Course lecture slides

## Time Spent

Approximately 4 hours.

## Reflection

This week's practical activity helped me understand why child themes are important in WordPress development. I learned that editing a child theme is much safer than editing the parent theme because updates will not remove my customisations.

I also became more confident using the WordPress Site Editor to customise colours, typography, buttons, and layout. Overall, this practical activity improved my understanding of WordPress theme development and website design.
